  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Evidence-based lobby &amp; advocacy to support human rights protections for Syrian refugee garment workers. The goal of the project is to create evidence on the scope of issues facing Syrian refugees, and models on how problems can be remediated. Including among others: enhanced human rights due diligence requirements, enhanced access to remedy and an enhanced remediation system. The evidence will be used to support advocacy to create sustainable, large-scale solutions for Syrians employed in the garment industry.</narrative>
  </description>
